description: A murderous creature, a mad scientist, romantic friends, and ancient ruins... what more could a girl-detective ask for?

description: A power-crazed pharaoh! A mad scientist! Rampaging clones! A damsel in distress! The military! Gunfire! Screaming! And, even a few panels of AYA! What a way to close a story arc!
Contains : Uncanny X-Men (2012) #12
Contains : Wolverine and the X-Men (2011) #10,11

Get ready for Rod Espinosa's incredible adaptation of this timeless classic. The Eisner-nominated creator of such critically acclaimed, sweeping epics as Neotopia and The Courageous Princess applies his visionary hand to this time-honored tale of an adventurous young girl who is swept into a strange magical fantasyland. Is it real or a dream? Journey down the rabbit hole in this amazing, lavishly illustrated, full-color rendition that is destined to become a new classic!

What happens when your guardian angel falls in love with you? After a traffic accident, Kyle Taylor is on the verge of death. His guardian angel Sarah makes a deal with the Angel of Death to save his life. Will it be something they'll both regret? And what's the Lord of Darkness have to do with it? An all-new shoujo series by the master of American manga, Ben Dunn!

Teen everyman Kyle Talyor is about to experience divine and demonic intervention, heralded by the appearance of Sarah, his Guardian Angel. She must protect him until it's time to face his "destiny," and whatever fate ultimately awaits him. Sinister forces have gathered to bring down the Kingdom of Heaven, and Kyle is caught on the front lines of a real Holy War!

Now that Kyle's destiny has been revealed, his training is about to begin. However, Samantha's sisters, Hope and Glory, suddenly arrive on Earth with a message from Kyle's mother, who is suffering in Limbo-plus to check out Samantha's new digs.
Cupid, Heaven's greatest soldier, begins Kyle's training to be a warrior paladin. Saving his mother from a high demon is Kyle's ultimate goal. Rescued or toast - it's all in the reflexes!

Kyle's training continues as he discovers the secret behind his mother's death and the forces working in both Heaven and Hell to control the fate of Mankind. Meanwhile, Kyle's father comes under the influence of an agent of the sinister Circle! Become a celestial convert when you read Heaven Sent!

Just as Kyle learns more about the places of men, angels, and demons in the world order, that order is about to change - with Kyle at the center of it all! To restore balance, Kyle must master the Soul Sword with archangel Michael's help so he can rescue his mother's soul from Purgatory!

Kyle's journey into the depths of Hell reveals much more than he anticipated. He begins to understand the intertwined nature of Good, Evil, and Mankind. He also meets the Journeyman, a mysterious wanderer who walks the grey line between what has been and what will be.

Kyle finally reaches his mother's soul, and Samantha reveals her past and her connections to both of them - secrets that involve the final fate of Mankind. Kyle realizes the role he's about to play in the battle between Heaven and Hell, and he doesn't like it one bit!

Kyle's homecoming isn't what he expected - the Earth has totally changed in his absence. The great apocalypse has occured, and Kyle is the only one who can save Mankind...but he doesn't want to do it! It's up to Samantha to convince him that Humanity can be saved.

Kyle has freed his mother's soul, and now he returns to Earth to lead the forces of Heaven against none other than the Anti-God. But the Earth he finds is facing the end times, brought on by a great disaster. Kyle must face the one responsible... his father.

The final battle between Heaven and the Anti-God concludes with the fate of Earth hanging in the balance. Kyle must make hard choices in order to save all that he knows and loves. But to muster the faith to defeat the foe, he'll need the secret only Samantha possesses!

description:
Richard Moore (Boneyard) cut his first teeth on this hard-driving fantasy western mini-series! Gorgeous but tough-as-nails elf Meg is a bounty hunter in a land that resembles the Old West... but this version is populated with elves, ogres, shape-shifters and creatures you can't even trust as far as you can throw them! Hey, it's a living, and Meg is darn good at it! But she and her bear companion Phil (who tends to be a bit less hot-blooded) just may have their hands full when they set out to capture Neil Voss, an elfin outlaw with a bounty of $10k on his head. But there's one big problem: he doesn't have a bear as a companion...he keeps company with a fire-breathing dragon the size of a house! With Moore's inimitable sense of timing, action, sexiness, and dry humor, this one is a guaranteed good time for all! This volume collects the first four-issue mini-series along with additional pin-up art and a new story, all printed in a larger format, better for showing off Moore's great artwork!

Collects Far West #1-4.
